From: lev-scottsdale <lev@alcor.org>
Date: Thu, 4 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] AArch64: Fix instruction selection for vector compare

The AArch64 instruction selector was incorrectly folding comparison
operations on vector types when the comparison result was used in
a scalar context. This caused miscompilation of code like:

  vbool = vec_cmp(x, y);
  if (vbool) { ... }

where the vector compare result was being incorrectly interpreted
as a scalar boolean.

The fix adds a check in AArch64ISelDAGToDAG to prevent folding
when the result type doesn't match the expected vector predicate
format.

Differential Revision: https://reviews.llvm.org/D123456
---
 llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp b/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp
index 123456..789abc 100644
--- a/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp
@@ -450,6 +450,16 @@ bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectCMP(SDValue &Cmp) {
   if (!Cmp.getValueType().isVector())
     return false;
   
+  // Don't fold if the comparison result is used in a scalar context.
+  // The vector predicate result must be extracted with CMEQ/CMGT etc
+  // before it can be used as a scalar boolean.
+  for (SDNode *User : Cmp->users()) {
+    if (User->getValueType(0).isScalarInteger()) {
+      // Leave the comparison unfolded for proper extraction
+      return false;
+    }
+  }
+
   // Existing vector compare handling...
   return true;
 }
